    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-12 text-center">The Journey</h2>

        <div class="space-y-8 text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            I started my career at IBM, developing compilers and leading QA automation
            teams. That early exposure to low-level systems thinking shaped how I approach
            problems ‚Äî always understanding what's happening beneath the abstractions.
          </p>

          <p>
            After IBM, I founded SoBe Tech Guru, providing data recovery and IT services.
            Working directly with clients taught me the importance of trust, reliability,
            and clear communication ‚Äî principles I carry into every project.
          </p>

          <p>
            In 2015, I founded Emergent Solutions to explore a question that had been
            growing in my mind: <strong class="text-section-primary">How does intelligence emerge from
            distributed systems?</strong>
          </p>

          <p>
            That question led me deep into AI research, consciousness studies, and
            distributed systems architecture. Along the way, I've built production systems
            serving millions of requests, conducted original research into abstract reasoning,
            and developed frameworks for autonomous agent coordination.
          </p>

          <p>
            Music has been a constant throughout. Composition and production offer a different
            lens on the same questions ‚Äî how do individual elements combine to create
            something greater than their sum? The same principles that guide my technical
            work apply to creating immersive sonic experiences.
          </p>

          <p class="text-lg text-accent">
            Today, my work integrates all these threads: building systems that are technically
            excellent, theoretically grounded, and fundamentally aimed at enabling new forms
            of intelligence to emerge.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
